<PageLayout title="About" description="About Mettadata Garden">
  <p>
    Mettadata Garden is a digital garden — a collection of interconnected notes
    and ideas that grow and evolve over time.
  </p>
  <p>
    Unlike a traditional blog where posts are published in chronological order,
    a digital garden organizes knowledge by topic and growth stage. Notes start
    as seeds, develop into sprouts and saplings, and eventually become evergreen
    reference material.
  </p>
  <h2>Gardens</h2>
  <p>Notes are organized into thematic gardens:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Professional</strong> — career, leadership, and industry knowledge</li>
    <li><strong>Spiritual</strong> — philosophy, mindfulness, and inner development</li>
    <li><strong>Academic</strong> — research, study notes, and formal knowledge</li>
  </ul>
  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <p>
    Notes link to each other using <code>[[wikilinks]]</code>, forming a web of
    interconnected ideas. You can explore by following links, browsing gardens,
    or searching.
  </p>
</PageLayout>
